Split scene. Left: a Regency-era cropping frame and a raised sledgehammer, charcoal with a burnt-orange impact star, and a plain date banner. Right: a modern desk with a human silhouette facing a loose cluster of small agent orbs drawn FLAT MATTE teal (no gloss, no specular highlights, no 3D shading), same composition mirrored. Between the halves a balance scale, tipped, with BOTH pans completely empty and unlabelled. Do NOT write HUMAN COST, SYSTEMIC INTEGRATION, or any tag on or near the scale.
TEXT (exactly, each once): headline "WHO BEARS THE TRANSITION?"; left date "1812"; right date "2026"; left caption "they asked for a managed transition and were refused"; right caption "this time the mechanisms can be built into the substrate".
